      <Value><![CDATA[<p><span class="lead-big"><strong>5 September 2022</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>To students:</strong></p>
<p>Dear students</p>
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Protecting yourself and others from COVID this new academic year </strong></span></p>
<p>As you will know from previous communications,<strong> we anticipate the delivery of our learning and teaching this year to be much as it was prior to the pandemic, while retaining some of the recent technological developments where those developments enhance the student </strong><strong>experience</strong><strong> (</strong><a href="/coronavirus/applicants/"><strong>more details available on our website</strong></a><strong>). </strong>You will be pleased to know that Students’ Union events and activities will run as normal too, without COVID restrictions.</p>
<p>Although all COVID rules and restrictions have been lifted in Scotland, the virus has not gone away. </p>
<p>Please use 'COVID sense' to help protect yourself and others, and to reduce pressure on health services. This means that you should:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.nhsinform.scot/covid-19-vaccine/"><strong>Get your vaccine </strong></a>when offered to ensure you are fully protected. NHS Inform has a <a href="https://www.nhsinform.scot/vaccinesforstudents">website specifically for students with information on how to get vaccinated</a> against COVID and other diseases.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.nhsinform.scot/illnesses-and-conditions/infections-and-poisoning/coronavirus-covid-19/coronavirus-covid-19"><strong>Stay at home </strong></a><strong>if you’re unwell</strong> with symptoms or have a fever (see our <a href="/coronavirus/faqs/accommodation/"><strong>Accommodation coronavirus FAQs</strong></a><strong> </strong>for advice if you live on campus).  You no longer have to report COVID illness to the University, but you do still need to tell us via the <a href="/study-here/learning-facilities/it-services/qmu-portal/">Student Portal</a> if any illness means that you will be absent from classes.</li>
<li><strong>Open windows</strong> when socialising indoors.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.gov.scot/publications/coronavirus-covid-19-staying-safe-and-protecting-others/pages/face-coverings/">Where appropriate, wear a face covering </a>in indoor public places and on public transport. (<strong>While you are not required to wear a face covering on campus, we would support those who choose to do so.)</strong></li>
<li><strong>Keep your hands clean </strong>by washing them regularly throughout the day and using the hand gel at sanitiser stations on campus.</li>
</ul>
<p>There is no requirement this year to ‘test before travel’ when you move into University accommodation (but do stay home if you’re unwell with symptoms).</p>
<p><strong>For </strong><a href="https://www.nhsinform.scot/illnesses-and-conditions/infections-and-poisoning/coronavirus-covid-19/coronavirus-covid-19-general-advice"><strong>advice on symptoms and what to do if you think you have coronavirus, visit NHS Inform</strong></a>.</p>
<p>We continue to keep our <a href="/coronavirus">coronavirus website</a> up to date with University-specific COVID advice, including <a href="/coronavirus/faqs/">FAQs</a>. Our COVID inbox remains open for any COVID-related questions not covered on our website (<a href="mailto:CovidHelp@qmu.ac.uk">CovidHelp@qmu.ac.uk</a>).</p>
<p>Thank you for your support in following COVID sense.</p>
<p>Wishing you a happy and fulfilling academic year.</p>
<p style="font-weight: 400;">Malcolm G Cutt </p>
<p style="font-weight: 400;">Director of Finance &amp; Corporate Strategic Development </p>
<p><strong>To staff:</strong></p>
<p>Dear colleagues</p>
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Protecting yourself and others from COVID this new academic year </strong></span></p>
<p>With the new academic year about to begin, I am writing to update you on the University’s advice on COVID. A similar message is being issued to students, which you can find on the <a href="/coronavirus/updates/">updates for students and staff</a> section of our coronavirus website.</p>
<p>As you will know from previous communications,<strong> we anticipate the delivery of our learning and teaching this academic year to be much as it was prior to the pandemic, while retaining some of the recent technological developments where those developments enhance the student experience </strong>(<a href="/coronavirus/applicants/">more details available on our website</a>). Students’ Union events and activities will run as normal, without COVID restrictions.</p>
<p>Although all COVID rules and restrictions have been lifted in Scotland, the virus has not gone away, as we all know. </p>
<p>Please continue to use 'COVID sense' to help protect yourself and others, and to reduce pressure on health services. This means that you should:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.nhsinform.scot/covid-19-vaccine/"><strong>Get your vaccine </strong></a>when offered to ensure you are fully protected. </li>
<li><a href="https://www.nhsinform.scot/illnesses-and-conditions/infections-and-poisoning/coronavirus-covid-19/coronavirus-covid-19"><strong>Stay at home </strong></a><strong>if you’re unwell</strong>with symptoms or have a fever.  You no longer have to report to Security and HR if you test positive for COVID, but you do, of course, still need to report sickness absence as per the sickness absence management policy and procedure.</li>
<li><strong>Open windows</strong> when socialising indoors.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.gov.scot/publications/coronavirus-covid-19-staying-safe-and-protecting-others/pages/face-coverings/">Where appropriate, wear a face covering </a>in indoor public places and on public transport. (<strong>While you are not required to wear a face covering on campus, we would support those who choose to do so.)</strong></li>
<li><strong>Keep your hands clean </strong>by washing them regularly throughout the day and using the hand gel at sanitiser stations on campus.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>For</strong> <a href="https://www.nhsinform.scot/illnesses-and-conditions/infections-and-poisoning/coronavirus-covid-19/coronavirus-covid-19-general-advice"><strong>advice on symptoms and what to do if you think you have coronavirus, visit NHS Inform</strong></a>.</p>
<p>We continue to keep our <a href="/coronavirus">coronavirus website</a> up to date with University-specific COVID advice, including <a href="/coronavirus/faqs/">FAQS</a>. Our COVID inbox remains open for any COVID-related questions not covered on our website (<a href="mailto:CovidHelp@qmu.ac.uk">CovidHelp@qmu.ac.uk</a>).</p>
<p style="font-weight: 400;"> </p>
<p style="font-weight: 400;">Malcolm G Cutt </p>
<p style="font-weight: 400;">Director of Finance &amp; Corporate Strategic Development </p>]]></Value>
