      "udi": "umb://element/25923b1d17ce4a6f9ae96340c367579a",
      "title": "7 May 2021",
      "content": "<p aria-level=\"1\">7 May 2021</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Dear students,</p>\n<p>Conscious that many of you will now have finished year end assessments, I hope that you are finding some time to enjoy the increased opportunities to get about and socialise, while sticking to the coronavirus rules.</p>\n<p aria-level=\"2\">Latest information and advice from government</p>\n<p>Over the next few days, we expect to hear whether Scotland will move down to coronavirus protection level 2 on 17 May, as hoped.  For more information on what we can and can’t do at each coronavirus protection level, please see the <a href=\"https://www.gov.scot/publications/coronavirus-covid-19-protection-levels/\">Scottish Government website.</a></p>\n<p>Whether or not restrictions ease on 17 May, it is, of course, essential that we all continue to follow FACTS, that is: </p>\n<ul>\n<li data-leveltext=\"\" data-font=\"Symbol\" data-listid=\"2\" aria-setsize=\"-1\" data-aria-posinset=\"1\" data-aria-level=\"1\">Wear <strong>F</strong>ace coverings   </li>\n<li data-leveltext=\"\" data-font=\"Symbol\" data-listid=\"2\" aria-setsize=\"-1\" data-aria-posinset=\"2\" data-aria-level=\"1\"><strong>A</strong>void crowded spaces  </li>\n<li data-leveltext=\"\" data-font=\"Symbol\" data-listid=\"2\" aria-setsize=\"-1\" data-aria-posinset=\"3\" data-aria-level=\"1\"><strong>C</strong>lean surfaces  </li>\n<li data-leveltext=\"\" data-font=\"Symbol\" data-listid=\"2\" aria-setsize=\"-1\" data-aria-posinset=\"4\" data-aria-level=\"1\">Maintain <strong>T</strong>wo metre social distancing  </li>\n<li data-leveltext=\"\" data-font=\"Symbol\" data-listid=\"2\" aria-setsize=\"-1\" data-aria-posinset=\"5\" data-aria-level=\"1\"><strong>S</strong>elf-isolate if you think you have COVID</li>\n</ul>\n<p aria-level=\"2\">Testing for students changing address at the end of semester </p>\n<p>While discussion on regular testing of students and staff continues, we have a firm plan to offer rapid lateral flow testing to students changing address at the end of the semester. This will help them protect their families and the wider community from COVID.</p>\n<p>We plan to run testing sessions on Friday 21 May and Tuesday 25 May, provisionally between 12 noon and 2pm, and encourage those participating to take two tests, one on each date, in line with the testing guidance.  We expect to be able provide more information and a link to the booking app around the middle of next week.</p>\n<p>Students living in central Edinburgh will still be able to be tested at a University of Edinburgh site, if that suits them better.  If you are an international student returning home, with your airline requiring a PCR test, you will need to obtain such a test privately.</p>\n<p aria-level=\"2\">Availability of regular rapid COVID testing for all people in Scotland</p>\n<p>Do also remember that everyone in Scotland can now order lateral flow tests online or collect them from a test site, for fast twice weekly testing at home. Around one in three people who have COVID-19 display no symptoms, which is one of the ways it can spread quickly to different people. That’s why being tested is so important. It protects everyone within your household and in our community. (<a href=\"https://www.gov.scot/publications/coronavirus-covid-19-getting-tested/pages/no-covid-symptoms/\">Find out how to obtain lateral flow test kits</a>).</p>\n<p>If you have symptoms of coronavirus: you should book a PCR test immediately - (<a href=\"https://www.gov.scot/publications/coronavirus-covid-19-getting-tested/pages/covid-symptoms/\">More information on how to book a test if you have symptoms</a>).</p>\n<p>Thank you for all your continued support. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Malcolm G Cutt </p>\n<p>Director of Operations and Finance </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Dear staff,</p>\n<p aria-level=\"2\">Latest information and advice from government</p>\n<p>Over the next few days, we expect to hear whether Scotland will move down to coronavirus protection level 2 on 17 May, as hoped.  For more information on what we can and can’t do at each coronavirus protection level, see the <a href=\"https://www.gov.scot/publications/coronavirus-covid-19-protection-levels/\">Scottish Government website</a>.</p>\n<p>Whether or not restrictions ease on 17 May, it is essential that we all continue to follow FACTS, ie:</p>\n<ul>\n<li data-leveltext=\"\" data-font=\"Symbol\" data-listid=\"2\" aria-setsize=\"-1\" data-aria-posinset=\"1\" data-aria-level=\"1\">Wear <strong>F</strong>ace coverings   </li>\n<li data-leveltext=\"\" data-font=\"Symbol\" data-listid=\"2\" aria-setsize=\"-1\" data-aria-posinset=\"2\" data-aria-level=\"1\"><strong>A</strong>void crowded space  </li>\n<li data-leveltext=\"\" data-font=\"Symbol\" data-listid=\"2\" aria-setsize=\"-1\" data-aria-posinset=\"3\" data-aria-level=\"1\"><strong>C</strong>lean surfaces  </li>\n<li data-leveltext=\"\" data-font=\"Symbol\" data-listid=\"2\" aria-setsize=\"-1\" data-aria-posinset=\"4\" data-aria-level=\"1\">Maintain<strong> </strong><strong>T</strong>wo metre social distancing  </li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li data-leveltext=\"\" data-font=\"Symbol\" data-listid=\"2\" aria-setsize=\"-1\" data-aria-posinset=\"1\" data-aria-level=\"1\"><strong>S</strong>elf-isolate if you think you have COVID </li>\n</ul>\n<p>Even if restrictions ease on the 17th, please remember that, until announced otherwise, staff should only visit campus for essential reasons or if you are unable to do your job effectively from home, and that attendance on campus should be agreed with your line manager. Even when staff need to be on campus, meetings should be held online rather than face to face except in exceptional circumstances. In addition, the need for cleaning etc means that meeting rooms need to be booked in advance.</p>\n<p>We anticipate that following yesterday’s elections, once the new Scottish Government ministerial team is in place, ongoing discussions between the Scottish Government and the higher education sector on preparations for the next academic year will gather pace.  Central items of discussion include planning assumptions for the autumn semester, quarantine of international students, and regular testing of students and staff. A paper outlining our planning assumptions for the next academic session, drawing on the Scottish Government discussions, and the resultant adjustments to learning and teaching, will be presented to Student Experience Committee on 19th May. </p>\n<p>Testing for students changing address at the end of semester</p>\n<p>While discussion on regular testing of students and staff continues, we have a firm plan to offer rapid lateral flow testing to students changing address at the end of the semester to help them protect their families and the wider community from COVID.  </p>\n<p>We plan to run testing sessions on Friday 21 May and Tuesday 25 May, provisionally between 12 noon and 2pm, and encourage those participating to take two tests, one on each date, in line with testing guidance.  We expect to be able provide more information and a link to the booking app around the middle of next week.  </p>\n<p>Students living in central Edinburgh will still be able to be tested at a University of Edinburgh site, if that suits them better.  International students returning home, with their airline requiring a PCR test, will need to obtain such a test privately.  </p>\n<p>Availability of regular rapid COVID testing for all people in Scotland</p>\n<p>Do also remember that everyone in Scotland can now order lateral flow tests online or collect them from a test site, for fast twice weekly testing at home. Around one in three people who have COVID-19 display no symptoms, which is one of the ways it can spread quickly to different people. That’s why being tested is so important. It protects everyone within your household and in our community. (<a href=\"https://www.gov.scot/publications/coronavirus-covid-19-getting-tested/pages/no-covid-symptoms/\">Find out how to obtain lateral flow test kits</a>). </p>\n<p>If you have symptoms of coronavirus: you should book a PCR test immediately - (<a href=\"https://www.gov.scot/publications/coronavirus-covid-19-getting-tested/pages/covid-symptoms/\">More information on how to book a test if you have symptoms</a>)</p>\n<p aria-level=\"2\">Staff stress survey</p>\n<p>Today is your last opportunity to complete the staff  <a href=\"https://qmu.onlinesurveys.ac.uk/stress-2\">stress survey</a>, Thank you to all of you who have responded so far.  At its next meeting, the Stress Management Working Group will review the summarised data and consider next steps.  </p>\n<p>Thank you for all your continued support at this very busy time of year.  </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Malcolm G Cutt </p>\n<p>Director of Operations and Finance </p>\n<p> </p>"
    },
